Trinity Industries, Inc. is a multi-industry company comprising five business groups: Rail Group, Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Construction Products Group, Inland Barge Group, and the Energy Equipment Group. These company groups provide products and services to the industrial,… MoreTrinity Industries, Inc. is a multi-industry company comprising five business groups: Rail Group, Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Construction Products Group, Inland Barge Group, and the Energy Equipment Group. These company groups provide products and services to the industrial, energy, transportation, and construction sectors. Founded in 1933, Trinity is based in Dallas, Texas. The company's businesses include Trinity Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Trinity Mining Services, Trinity Structural Towers, Inc., Trinity Heads, Inc., Trinity Logistics Group, Inc., McConway & Torley, LLC, Trinity Containers, LLC, Trinity Highway Products, LLC, Transit Mix Concrete & Materials Company.
Trinity Industries, Inc. is a multi-industry company comprising five business groups: Rail Group, Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Construction Products Group, Inland Barge Group, and the Energy Equipment Group. These company groups provide products and services to the industrial,… MoreTrinity Industries, Inc. is a multi-industry company comprising five business groups: Rail Group, Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Construction Products Group, Inland Barge Group, and the Energy Equipment Group. These company groups provide products and services to the industrial, energy, transportation, and construction sectors. Founded in 1933, Trinity is based in Dallas, Texas. The company's businesses include Trinity Railcar Leasing and Management Services Group, Trinity Mining Services, Trinity Structural Towers, Inc., Trinity Heads, Inc., Trinity Logistics Group, Inc., McConway & Torley, LLC, Trinity Containers, LLC, Trinity Highway Products, LLC, Transit Mix Concrete & Materials Company.

IT Structure
•The IT department of Trinity Industries, Inc. is responsible for IT functions for the company and most of its subsidiaries.
•Other subsidiaries, mainly within the construction products group, outsource IT functions.
•Trinity has an outsourcing partnership with Dell Services. 

IT Intelligence Snippets
2013:
•Adopting ITIL v3 and deploying ITSM.
•Upgraded its Oracle financials software.

2012:
•Trinity Industries, Inc. plans to implement serial projects in different areas of the IT department.





